According to the documentation you can pass a string to the overlay parameter in options when generating urls and image tags:
`cloudinary.url("mountain.jpg", { overlay: "cloudinary_icon", width: 100 })`

While this works fine for images in the root folder, it fails when trying to overlay images from subfolders:
`cloudinary.url("mountain.jpg", { overlay: "sub/cloudinary_icon", width: 100 })`

Now, there is a workaround which works fine:
`cloudinary.url("mountain.jpg", { overlay: { public_id: "sub/cloudinary_icon" }, width: 100 })`

This however, is not described in the docs. At least I only figured it out by looking at the code.

